    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-and-pepper-teriyaki-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until slightly softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-and-pepper-teriyaki-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pepper is cooking, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-and-pepper-teriyaki-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper has softened, add your <strong>meat-free chick'n</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until warmed through and starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-and-pepper-teriyaki-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the<strong> chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>brown sugar </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-and-pepper-teriyaki-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong> to the meat-free chick'n and stir to combine</p><p>Cook for 4-5 min further or until the sauce has reduced to a sticky consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>meat-free chick'n & pepper</strong> <strong>teriyaki</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s] </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-and-pepper-teriyaki-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>meat-free chick'n & pepper teriyaki </strong>from the heat and add your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong> to the pan</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-and-pepper-teriyaki-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>meat-free chick'n & pepper teriyaki</strong> over the <strong>cooked rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
